1
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:40,533
Manuel's paralyzed.

2
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:42,567
He's no use to you anymore.

3
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,533
You can divorce him anytime.

4
00:00:44,667 --> 00:00:45,767
If you hadn't been shot,

5
00:00:45,900 --> 00:00:48,367
would you have stuck with the
separation from Mom?

6
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:51,267
I had already made up my mind
to leave your mom.

7
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:52,967
Noah, maybe it's better

8
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:54,400
if we don't go through with
the wedding.

9
00:00:54,533 --> 00:00:57,200
I'll do everything I can to earn
Felma's forgiveness,

10
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:58,467
and our children's, too.

11
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:00,467
I'll do whatever it takes
to bring you back home

12
00:01:00,600 --> 00:01:01,267
to the Philippines.

13
00:01:01,400 --> 00:01:04,100
Let's watch Coleen's video.

14
00:01:04,867 --> 00:01:05,867
Hazel.

15
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:06,567
Don't tell me this is your
daughter too, Manuel?

16
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:07,600
Is this your idea?

17
00:01:07,767 --> 00:01:08,533
You're so ungrateful!

18
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:09,433
Hazel!

19
00:01:09,567 --> 00:01:10,833
Hazel, don't hurt Jessica!

20
00:01:10,967 --> 00:01:11,800
What now?

21
00:01:11,933 --> 00:01:13,100
If I could walk away from
this wedding,

22
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:16,500
that only means you're not
the priority in my life.

23
00:01:16,633 --> 00:01:18,533
And who, Mom? Your ex-husband?

24
00:01:18,667 --> 00:01:21,133
I want to believe your decision
has nothing to do with Manuel.

25
00:01:21,267 --> 00:01:22,467
It has really nothing to do
with him.

26
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,267
I waited for you.

27
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,500
I didn't give up on you.

28
00:01:25,633 --> 00:01:26,600
And after everything,

29
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:27,967
you're going to throw me away
just like that?

30
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:30,000
I don't want to be manipulated.

31
00:01:30,133 --> 00:01:31,133
What do you mean?

32
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:33,500
When Manuel called, you were
the one who decided

33
00:01:33,633 --> 00:01:35,800
whether I should answer or not.

34
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:38,633
I don't like being told what to
do.

35
00:01:38,767 --> 00:01:40,500
I want to make decisions
for myself.

36
00:01:40,667 --> 00:01:48,733
I want to be the one in control
of my choices, of my life!

37
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:58,333
Don't make me feel like I don't
care because if that's true,

38
00:01:58,467 --> 00:02:01,700
I would've left your father on
the street a long time ago!

39
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:04,700
I've always cared
for this family.

40
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,833
I'm the breadwinner.

41
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:08,900
It's all me!

42
00:02:09,033 --> 00:02:12,033
I pay the bills, I put food on
the table, and then your dad?

43
00:02:12,167 --> 00:02:13,300
What does he even do?

44
00:02:14,700 --> 00:02:16,167
What he's good at?

45
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,800
Being a janitor?

46
00:02:18,933 --> 00:02:21,967
Why? Will he able to feed us by
doing that?

47
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:25,167
Dad may not earn a lot,
but he still tried, Mom.

48
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:27,133
He's always the one beside me.

49
00:02:27,267 --> 00:02:29,967
Even if you took away
his right to work.

50
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,600
I got to grow up with him.

51
00:02:32,733 --> 00:02:36,533
I grew up full of love and care.

52
00:02:36,667 --> 00:02:38,500
And he never lied to me.

53
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:39,800
He never laid a hand on me.

54
00:02:39,933 --> 00:02:42,933
So, don't be surprised
that my loyalty is with him!

55
00:02:43,067 --> 00:02:44,567
You are such an ungrateful kid!

56
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,733
Hazel!

57
00:02:45,867 --> 00:02:46,967
Hazel!

58
00:02:48,967 --> 00:02:50,733
The nerve of you to talk back
to me like that!

59
00:02:50,867 --> 00:02:51,933
Hazel!

60
00:02:52,067 --> 00:02:54,633
I didn't want to hurt you,
but why are you like this?

61
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:00,567
- See?
- Hazel.

62
00:03:00,700 --> 00:03:02,300
Hazel, stop! Don't hurt Jessica!

63
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:03,967
You see?

64
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:06,433
You've seen how she talks back
to me, right?

65
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:08,700
Because you allow it!

66
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:13,000
You, too! You're just as guilty!
You're enabling this kid!

67
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:16,567
She should be taught
a lesson, you know?

68
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:19,800
- Hazel, stop!
- She should be taught a lesson!

69
00:03:20,433 --> 00:03:21,867
For heaven's sake!

70
00:03:22,033 --> 00:03:22,833
Shut up!

71
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:23,933
- No!
- You're disturbing the peace-

72
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:25,267
- You shut up!

73
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,400
Get out!

74
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:28,867
Hazel, stop!
This is embarrassing.

75
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,467
Isn't this kid's behavior
more shameful?

76
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,800
What do you think? Isn't it
more shameful?

77
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:35,600
- Please stop.
- You see?

78
00:03:35,733 --> 00:03:39,133
You raised her, right? And this
is how she talks back to me now!

79
00:03:39,267 --> 00:03:41,767
Like I'm the one who doesn't
care about this family!

80
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:42,800
We didn't say anything
like that.

81
00:03:42,933 --> 00:03:45,133
- Please stop.
- Is that it, Manuel?

82
00:03:45,267 --> 00:03:45,900
Madame?

83
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:47,600
Please refrain from shouting.

84
00:03:47,733 --> 00:03:50,200
We do not tolerate such
behavior here.

85
00:03:50,333 --> 00:03:51,633
I don't care!

86
00:03:51,767 --> 00:03:52,900
I'm a paying client!

87
00:03:53,033 --> 00:03:53,833
Yes, but-

88
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,033
You don't get to tell me what
to do!

89
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:57,200
You are disturbing
a very sick patient!

90
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:59,000
I don't care about that!

91
00:03:59,133 --> 00:04:00,800
This is a family matter!

92
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,267
Can't you see
we're talking here?

93
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,500
- And this is my daughter.
- Enough! Enough!

94
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:05,400
No!

95
00:04:05,533 --> 00:04:07,867
Don't touch me! I'm not
yet done!

96
00:04:08,933 --> 00:04:09,933
Don't touch me!

97
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:11,433
No!

98
00:04:15,333 --> 00:04:17,367
Mr. Manuel, are you okay?

99
00:04:19,267 --> 00:04:20,500
Dad!

100
00:04:32,467 --> 00:04:34,267
Mom, please.

101
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,733
Take back what you
said to Uncle Noah.

102
00:04:36,867 --> 00:04:39,267
Mom, we know you just
acted on impulse.

103
00:04:40,067 --> 00:04:42,367
I'm not taking back what I said.

104
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,367
That's my decision.

105
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,033
And I didn't act on impulse.

106
00:04:48,167 --> 00:04:52,467
When you ambushed me and
forced me to face Noah...

107
00:04:53,467 --> 00:04:56,900
Kids, I'm not a teenager
anymore!

108
00:04:57,033 --> 00:04:59,033
Do you really have to set
me up with my boyfriend

109
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:00,767
just so I'd get back with him?

110
00:05:04,767 --> 00:05:10,567
I know you all think Noah
is the right one for me.

111
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:17,067
But did any of you ever ask how
I feel?

112
00:05:20,700 --> 00:05:21,867
No!

113
00:05:23,100 --> 00:05:25,333
I considered your feelings.

114
00:05:25,467 --> 00:05:28,167
But in the end, the final say
is still mine.

115
00:05:28,300 --> 00:05:31,400
This is my life. I'm the one
who decides.

116
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:33,200
You need to respect that!

117
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:34,767
But, Mom, we just don't
understand

118
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:36,800
why you suddenly changed
your mind.

119
00:05:36,933 --> 00:05:38,933
You always said your ex had
nothing to do

120
00:05:39,067 --> 00:05:41,233
with your sudden backing
out of the wedding.

121
00:05:41,367 --> 00:05:42,900
Then why is it only now that
you're changing your mind,

122
00:05:43,033 --> 00:05:45,967
right after something happened
with that guy in Canada?

123
00:05:46,767 --> 00:05:51,400
You know the reason why Noah and
I broke up, don't you?

124
00:05:51,533 --> 00:05:55,267
When he asked me for space,
that's when I realized

125
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:59,467
I can't commit to Noah,
or anyone else.

126
00:06:00,367 --> 00:06:01,000
But, Mom-

127
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:03,533
I've said what I needed to say.

128
00:06:03,667 --> 00:06:05,700
Just rest now.

129
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:30,733
<i>You always said your ex
had nothing to do with</i>

130
00:06:30,867 --> 00:06:33,067
<i>your sudden backing
out of the wedding.</i>

131
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,733
<i>Then why is it only now
that you're changing your mind,</i>

132
00:06:34,867 --> 00:06:37,867
<i>right after something happened
with that guy in Canada?</i>

133
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,433
Mom?

134
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:52,533
I'm sorry for conniving
with my siblings.

135
00:06:52,667 --> 00:06:58,767
I'm sorry I didn't ask
how you felt about all of this.

136
00:06:58,900 --> 00:07:02,067
I feel guilty, Mom.

137
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:08,167
Like, I'm the reason why you and
Uncle Noah broke up.

138
00:07:08,300 --> 00:07:09,867
About...

139
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:14,100
those times I kept bothering you
about Dad.

140
00:07:19,367 --> 00:07:22,500
You have a right to your dad.

141
00:07:22,633 --> 00:07:24,867
Don't blame yourself.

142
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,700
Maybe your nagging
actually helped me.

143
00:07:28,833 --> 00:07:34,000
It made me realize what my
feelings for Noah really are.

144
00:07:34,133 --> 00:07:36,667
Whatever it is I want
in my life.

145
00:07:36,800 --> 00:07:40,000
But, Mom, I was just thinking.

146
00:07:40,133 --> 00:07:44,900
If you told Uncle Noah
you're not ready to commit yet,

147
00:07:45,033 --> 00:07:48,033
what if Dad tries to get back
with you?

148
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,100
That won't happen.

149
00:07:52,067 --> 00:07:54,400
He's married to Hazel.

150
00:07:54,533 --> 00:07:56,200
And even if they separate,

151
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:59,733
I have no intention of getting
back with him.

152
00:07:59,867 --> 00:08:02,233
I don't love your dad anymore.

153
00:08:03,767 --> 00:08:08,133
So, can we just stop this?

154
00:08:08,267 --> 00:08:10,367
Weren't you the one who said

155
00:08:10,500 --> 00:08:13,633
you were content to have met
your dad?

156
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,900
Sweetie, that's where it ends.

157
00:08:16,033 --> 00:08:20,733
Don't hold on to hopes of having
a relationship with your dad.

158
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:21,767
What?

159
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:24,633
But, Mom, Dad's in bad shape
right now.

160
00:08:24,767 --> 00:08:27,600
Can't I at least check on him?

161
00:08:27,733 --> 00:08:29,533
No!

162
00:08:29,667 --> 00:08:32,033
Well, then I'll just get
updates from Jessica.

163
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:34,867
She's kind anyway.

164
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,833
Hazel isn't.

165
00:08:36,967 --> 00:08:38,767
I've already indulged
you enough.

166
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,333
That's enough!

167
00:08:41,733 --> 00:08:45,767
- But-
- Don't let your dad's life...

168
00:08:45,900 --> 00:08:48,700
and his family fall apart
because of you.

169
00:08:48,833 --> 00:08:50,467
Or because of me!

170
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,533
But, Mom...

171
00:08:51,667 --> 00:08:53,500
Please don't insist anymore!

172
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:57,633
Just be content that
you've at least made

173
00:08:57,767 --> 00:09:00,867
some kind of connection with
your dad.

174
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,367
Dad, are you okay?

175
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,900
Are you not feeling well?

176
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:32,200
No, dear. I'm okay.

177
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:38,200
But the administrator talked
to me.

178
00:09:38,333 --> 00:09:39,367
Apparently, a lot of people have
been complaining

179
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,667
about our fights.

180
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:43,533
Don't worry, Dad.

181
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:46,833
I'll talk to the administrators
and apologize.

182
00:09:46,967 --> 00:09:50,267
Yeah, but my PSW said
the patients here

183
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:54,067
already started a petition to
have me kicked out.

184
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,767
Oh, no.

185
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:28,467
- Uncle.
- Uncle.

186
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,433
How are you?

187
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,433
How are you doing?

188
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:49,167
I'm sorry, Uncle.

189
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:55,267
Our plan to have you and Mom
talk backfired on us.

190
00:10:56,767 --> 00:10:58,533
I'm confused.

191
00:11:01,033 --> 00:11:03,533
I don't know what I did wrong.

192
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,667
Or what I'm lacking.

193
00:11:12,267 --> 00:11:15,567
I did nothing but love your mom.

194
00:11:15,700 --> 00:11:17,567
We know all that, Uncle.

195
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:20,500
The problem isn't with you.

196
00:11:20,633 --> 00:11:23,967
Besides, none of this would
have happened

197
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:27,967
if Coleen's dad hadn't
approached and talked to Mom.

198
00:11:28,100 --> 00:11:30,000
And you too, Uncle.

199
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:32,767
Why did you give Mom space?

200
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,567
Look what happened? She started
imagining all sorts of things.

201
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:37,600
Andrea, don't blame Uncle.

202
00:11:37,733 --> 00:11:40,533
I'm just saying, Jeff.

203
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:41,800
Enough already.

204
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:43,967
You two might start fighting.

205
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:46,033
But don't worry, Uncle.

206
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:48,833
We won't give up.

207
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:50,867
We'll do whatever it takes.

208
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:55,467
Every possible way to change
Mom's mind.

209
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:06,000
Okay, Ma'am. Thank you
very much.

210
00:12:08,867 --> 00:12:13,700
Mom, there's a problem
at the nursing home.

211
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,567
Yes, I know.

212
00:12:15,733 --> 00:12:17,467
I got an email from
the administrator.

213
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,200
They want your dad out.

214
00:12:20,400 --> 00:12:22,067
They already did?

215
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,433
Yeah.

216
00:12:24,233 --> 00:12:26,800
After a week, they said your dad
shouldn't be there anymore.

217
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:29,167
This is your fault, both of you.

218
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:30,567
Why us?

219
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:31,967
You're the one who started
the fights.

220
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:34,100
You're the one who caused
all the trouble there.

221
00:12:34,233 --> 00:12:36,233
You're the reason I lost it.

222
00:12:36,367 --> 00:12:37,500
You and your useless father.

223
00:12:37,633 --> 00:12:39,100
Don't call him that!

224
00:12:39,233 --> 00:12:40,533
He's not useless!

225
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:41,500
So what is he then?

226
00:12:41,633 --> 00:12:43,133
He can't walk,
can't do anything,

227
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:44,767
and contributes nothing!

228
00:12:44,900 --> 00:12:46,600
So, isn't he useless?

229
00:12:46,733 --> 00:12:48,133
Can you please not get me
worked up?

230
00:12:48,300 --> 00:12:50,367
I have a job interview.

231
00:12:50,500 --> 00:12:51,367
Mom, wait.

232
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:54,167
Which nursing home
are we moving Dad to?

233
00:12:54,300 --> 00:12:56,333
I don't know and
I don't care!

234
00:12:56,467 --> 00:12:58,433
It's up to you. If you want,
you can find one.

235
00:12:58,567 --> 00:12:59,733
Just don't bring him back
here because I'm the one

236
00:12:59,867 --> 00:13:01,933
who'll have to deal
with it again.

237
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,933
Dad is being kicked out of
the nursing home,

238
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:24,567
and Mom refuses to take him back
to our house.

239
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:27,400
I spent the entire day searching
for a new home,

240
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:29,600
but I couldn't find one.

241
00:13:29,733 --> 00:13:32,900
Oh, dear. That's just awful.

242
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:36,000
We'll see around
if anyone can help.

243
00:13:36,133 --> 00:13:39,967
Mrs. Wilson, Mr. Wilson,
can Dad stay here?

244
00:13:40,100 --> 00:13:43,000
I'll visit him every day,
I promise.

245
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:44,733
We'd love to help you, Jessica.

246
00:13:44,867 --> 00:13:46,900
We're just not equipped
to help your dad.

247
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:51,133
We just don't have the proper
medical equipment at the moment.

248
00:13:51,267 --> 00:13:54,067
What we can do is cover all
the costs

249
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:57,333
once you find a nursing home
for him.

250
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,367
Where did you get those bruises
from?

251
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,233
It's Mom.

252
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:10,367
She hurt me and Dad.

253
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:12,133
Dear Lord!

254
00:14:12,267 --> 00:14:16,100
We should report her to the
child protection services.

255
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:19,300
No, no, Mrs. Wilson.
No, please. No.

256
00:14:19,433 --> 00:14:21,500
But she's hurting you, Jessica.

257
00:14:21,633 --> 00:14:24,067
But she's still my mom.

258
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:27,333
And to be fair to her,
she's been through a lot, too.

259
00:14:27,467 --> 00:14:29,967
She's pressured and stressed.

260
00:14:30,133 --> 00:14:31,733
She just lost control.

261
00:14:31,867 --> 00:14:33,700
I don't want to put her
in trouble.

262
00:14:33,833 --> 00:14:36,267
I don't want to send her to
jail. Please.

263
00:14:36,400 --> 00:14:38,000
You poor thing.

264
00:14:38,133 --> 00:14:41,333
You're such a good-hearted
daughter.

265
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:46,833
What we can do is if you find a
new nursing home for him,

266
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:48,433
you can stay here.

267
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:49,733
I agree.

268
00:14:49,867 --> 00:14:53,267
But we stand by and don't let
you be hurt by your own mother.

269
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:56,067
Thank you, Mr. and Mrs. Wilson.

270
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,567
I really appreciate it.

271
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,300
What is it, dear?

272
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:06,667
I just realized that
if I stay here,

273
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:09,400
that will just make Mom
even angrier.

274
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:11,767
She won't stop looking.

275
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:15,400
Anywhere Dad and I go,
she'll find us.

276
00:15:20,167 --> 00:15:22,033
Have you thought of going
back to the Philippines

277
00:15:22,167 --> 00:15:23,433
with your dad?

278
00:15:23,567 --> 00:15:26,933
I think that's what Manuel would
like to do.

279
00:15:27,067 --> 00:15:31,600
Actually, I did promise
Dad I'd find a way.

280
00:15:31,733 --> 00:15:34,500
But I don't know if
we can afford it.

281
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,900
We don't have money.

282
00:15:37,033 --> 00:15:40,300
We haven't even talked
about it yet.

283
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:42,000
We don't have a plan.

284
00:15:42,133 --> 00:15:45,333
Well, when you do, we will help.

285
00:15:45,467 --> 00:15:48,433
That's the least we can do
for Manuel.

286
00:15:48,567 --> 00:15:50,233
Thank you.

287
00:15:50,367 --> 00:15:52,900
Thank you, Mr. and Mrs. Wilson.

288
00:15:53,033 --> 00:15:55,533
Thank you.

289
00:15:55,667 --> 00:15:58,167
Thank you very much.

290
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:05,433
Angge.

291
00:16:05,567 --> 00:16:07,800
- Good morning, Ma'am.
- Good morning.

292
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:11,200
- Are you okay now?
- I am. Thank you, Ma'am.

293
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:18,067
Arlene, have the samples
been delivered yet?

294
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,500
Yes, Ma'am.

295
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,500
Okay, thank you.

296
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:25,633
For delivery, Ma'am. We need
your signature.

297
00:16:25,767 --> 00:16:26,567
For delivery?

298
00:16:26,700 --> 00:16:28,100
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Okay.

299
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:31,533
All right.

300
00:16:31,667 --> 00:16:33,233
- Thank you, Ma'am.
- Thank you okay.

301
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:52,733
Manuel really had a strong
effect on you, huh?

302
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,233
Canada's so far away.

303
00:16:55,367 --> 00:16:56,200
It's miles and miles away,

304
00:16:56,333 --> 00:16:59,633
but his influence on you
is something else.

305
00:17:00,367 --> 00:17:02,333
Knock it off, Paz.

306
00:17:03,067 --> 00:17:05,467
Manuel has nothing
to do with this.

307
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:08,900
Don't blame him.

308
00:17:16,100 --> 00:17:17,267
Hold on.

309
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:21,333
Why do I even have to explain
my decision to all of you?

310
00:17:22,733 --> 00:17:26,900
Because it just feels like
there's something going on.

311
00:17:27,033 --> 00:17:28,133
Right?

312
00:17:28,267 --> 00:17:31,500
Didn't it ever occur to you that
maybe even just a little,

313
00:17:31,633 --> 00:17:34,033
your decision was just plain
wrong?

314
00:17:34,167 --> 00:17:38,233
Because everyone around you
is saying the same thing.

315
00:17:38,367 --> 00:17:40,933
Didn't it ever occur to you
that everyone around you

316
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:41,867
is already being affected?

317
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:44,067
First and foremost...

318
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:47,433
your kids.

319
00:17:47,567 --> 00:17:51,733
Because they were hoping Noah
would become their dad.

320
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:54,233
They actually loved him.

321
00:17:54,367 --> 00:17:56,133
Second.

322
00:17:56,267 --> 00:17:59,600
This poor guy, Noah,
for heaven's sake.

323
00:17:59,733 --> 00:18:04,867
Even his work is being affected.
If he's not late, he's absent.

324
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:09,433
And I heard that the other night
he got drunk.

325
00:18:09,567 --> 00:18:11,267
Come on, Sis.

326
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:13,900
So you really can't blame me

327
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:16,933
for getting agitated with
Manuel, right?

328
00:18:17,067 --> 00:18:21,867
Because he's the root cause
of everything that's happening!

329
00:18:22,467 --> 00:18:26,367
Manuel has nothing to do with my
decision.

330
00:18:26,500 --> 00:18:28,567
Really? He doesn't?

331
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:29,800
You know what, Sis?

332
00:18:29,933 --> 00:18:32,033
I just feel like...

333
00:18:32,167 --> 00:18:34,567
you're in denial.

334
00:18:35,633 --> 00:18:38,300
There it is. I knew it.

335
00:18:38,433 --> 00:18:41,100
You still love Manuel,
don't you?

336
00:18:41,233 --> 00:18:42,833
I knew it!

337
00:18:42,967 --> 00:18:46,100
Because honestly, the way
things suddenly changed?

338
00:18:46,233 --> 00:18:47,633
You were about to get married.

339
00:18:47,767 --> 00:18:52,167
You were getting married, and
yet you still changed your mind!

340
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:55,133
There's definitely something
going on.

341
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:57,200
Girl, let's be real.

342
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:58,567
Just tell me the truth.

343
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,800
Before you go to sleep at night,
be honest...

344
00:19:00,933 --> 00:19:02,100
Who do you think about?

345
00:19:02,233 --> 00:19:07,433
Noah? Manuel? Who? Answer me!

346
00:19:07,567 --> 00:19:08,467
No one.

347
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,600
Really? Okay, then.

348
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:12,800
When you wake up in the morning,

349
00:19:12,933 --> 00:19:15,200
who's the first person
on your mind?

350
00:19:15,333 --> 00:19:16,933
Answer me.

351
00:19:17,067 --> 00:19:19,300
Well, well, well...

352
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:21,567
Don't mess with me.

353
00:19:29,700 --> 00:19:31,167
Just here, Sir.
Thank you.

354
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:33,367
What are you doing here?

355
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:36,933
I sent an email requesting
a week's extension

356
00:19:37,067 --> 00:19:38,300
while I'm looking
for a new nursing home.

357
00:19:38,433 --> 00:19:40,733
So, can't you wait?

358
00:19:40,867 --> 00:19:44,167
I'm sorry, Ma'am. We're just
following orders.

359
00:19:45,867 --> 00:19:47,433
No!

360
00:19:47,567 --> 00:19:48,467
- Take him back.
- Mom, what are you doing?

361
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:49,733
- Ma'am!
- Mom!

362
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:51,667
- Take him back!
- Mom!

363
00:19:52,367 --> 00:19:53,200
- Ma'am.
- What?

364
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:55,700
Please be gentle with the
patient.

365
00:19:56,233 --> 00:19:57,500
Mom, enough.

366
00:20:02,933 --> 00:20:03,633
No, I said, take him back!

367
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:04,800
- I don't want him here!
- Mom!

368
00:20:04,933 --> 00:20:06,033
- Stop it!
- Stop it!

369
00:20:06,167 --> 00:20:07,533
Mom, what are you doing?

370
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:10,467
Ma'am, stop it, or we will call
the police.

371
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:12,200
Mom, stop it!

372
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:15,933
I'll take it from here, Sir.
Thank you.

373
00:20:18,733 --> 00:20:19,900
Mom, don't worry.

374
00:20:20,033 --> 00:20:23,667
I'll take care of Dad until we
find him a new nursing home.

375
00:20:24,167 --> 00:20:26,233
What are you talking about?

376
00:20:26,667 --> 00:20:28,200
You have school.

377
00:20:28,333 --> 00:20:29,833
And what about me?

378
00:20:29,967 --> 00:20:31,933
I'm busy looking for a new job!

379
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:34,100
Who's gonna take care of him?

380
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:36,400
What if he's alone here?

381
00:20:36,567 --> 00:20:38,800
What if he needs to pee or poop?

382
00:20:38,933 --> 00:20:41,033
Is the house going to be
a mess again?

383
00:20:41,167 --> 00:20:42,133
Is this place going
to stink again?

384
00:20:42,267 --> 00:20:43,833
Mom, what's wrong with you?

385
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:45,767
Why do you have to say that
in front of Dad?

386
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:47,700
Because that's the truth!

387
00:20:47,833 --> 00:20:49,033
It has happened before.

388
00:20:49,167 --> 00:20:51,200
It will happen over
and over again!

389
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:54,200
Someone needs to look after
him 24/7!

390
00:20:54,333 --> 00:20:56,200
Hazel.

391
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:58,700
I won't let that happen.

392
00:21:02,967 --> 00:21:04,667
Really?

393
00:21:05,533 --> 00:21:07,133
Really, Manuel?

394
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,367
You can't even
move your legs.

395
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,700
How do you expect to
control your bladder?

396
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,467
<i> Mom, please.</i>

397
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:54,933
<i>Take back what you
said to Uncle Noah.</i>

398
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:57,400
<i>Mom, we know you just
acted on impulse.</i>

399
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,533
<i> Then why is it only now
that you're changing your</i> mind,

400
00:22:11,667 --> 00:22:14,400
<i>right after something happened
with that guy in Canada?</i>

401
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:22,367
<i> I feel guilty, Mom.</i>

402
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:28,733
<i>Like, I'm the reason why you
and Uncle Noah broke up.</i>

403
00:22:29,500 --> 00:22:33,667
<i>About those times I kept
bothering you about Dad.</i>

404
00:22:35,233 --> 00:22:37,667
<i> You're in denial.</i>

405
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,933
<i>You still love Manuel,
don't you?</i>

406
00:22:41,067 --> 00:22:42,600
<i> I knew it!</i>

407
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:45,967
<i>Because honestly, the way things
suddenly changed?</i>

408
00:22:46,100 --> 00:22:50,033
<i>You were about to get married.
You were getting married!</i>

409
00:22:53,367 --> 00:22:54,367
Mom!

410
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:56,100
Uncle Noah is outside.

411
00:22:56,233 --> 00:22:57,300
He's drunk.

412
00:22:57,433 --> 00:22:58,533
What?

413
00:22:58,667 --> 00:23:00,300
Felma!

414
00:23:01,567 --> 00:23:03,433
Felma!

415
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,800
Felma, can we talk, please?

416
00:23:08,933 --> 00:23:09,967
Noah?

417
00:23:10,100 --> 00:23:12,133
Noah, what are you doing here?

418
00:23:12,267 --> 00:23:14,367
You're not answering my calls!

419
00:23:14,500 --> 00:23:16,167
My messages, you don't...

420
00:23:16,300 --> 00:23:17,933
Can we talk?

421
00:23:18,067 --> 00:23:21,133
You're drunk. Just go home.

422
00:23:21,267 --> 00:23:22,633
I don't want to. No.

423
00:23:22,800 --> 00:23:23,667
Noah, that's enough.

424
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:25,167
- Uncle, please go home.
- You're just drunk.

425
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,733
Oh, no. The guard is here.

426
00:23:26,867 --> 00:23:29,467
I won't let this happen, Felma.
We need to talk, please!

427
00:23:29,600 --> 00:23:30,267
But didn't we already talk
about this?

428
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:31,867
I already told you everything.

429
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,733
- Let's just talk, Felma.
- Guard. Guard.

430
00:23:33,867 --> 00:23:35,233
Is there a problem?

431
00:23:35,367 --> 00:23:36,500
Guard, well...

432
00:23:36,633 --> 00:23:37,333
it's because...

433
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:38,133
- Guard...
- Can you please...

434
00:23:38,267 --> 00:23:40,033
Don't get involved here!

435
00:23:40,167 --> 00:23:41,800
Sir, I can't just stand
by and not get involved.

436
00:23:41,933 --> 00:23:43,500
You're causing trouble
for the residents here.

437
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:44,400
I said don't get involved!

438
00:23:44,533 --> 00:23:45,200
Noah, you're just drunk!

439
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:46,667
Don't touch me!

440
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:49,967
Noah! Don't!

441
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:51,700
Don't touch me!

442
00:23:53,333 --> 00:23:54,967
- Noah! Don't!
- Please stop!

443
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,133
- Let's go.
- Don't! Stop!

444
00:23:57,300 --> 00:23:58,400
Base. Base.

445
00:23:58,533 --> 00:24:01,067
There's someone causing trouble
here in Block 17, 2134.

446
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,500
Guard, guard, guard.

447
00:24:03,133 --> 00:24:04,267
No need, it's okay.

448
00:24:04,400 --> 00:24:05,533
I'll take care of him.

449
00:24:05,667 --> 00:24:07,533
Ma'am, I can't leave you alone
with him.

450
00:24:07,667 --> 00:24:08,667
Mister, it's okay now.

451
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:10,500
- Uncle Noah didn't mean it.
- Yeah, that's true.

452
00:24:10,633 --> 00:24:11,567
Sorry about that.

453
00:24:11,700 --> 00:24:13,500
- We'll take care of it.
- Sorry for the trouble.

454
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:14,900
- Alright.
- We're fine now.

455
00:24:21,067 --> 00:24:22,700
Noah, seriously?

456
00:24:22,833 --> 00:24:24,500
Even the guard?

457
00:24:24,633 --> 00:24:27,500
He wasn't even doing anything
to you, and you hurt him!

458
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:31,700
Good thing Coleen and I were
able to talk to him.

459
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:40,600
Here, have some coffee
first to sober up.

460
00:24:40,733 --> 00:24:44,133
And so you can get home
properly, too. Go on.

461
00:24:44,667 --> 00:24:47,600
I won't give up
on you, Felma.

462
00:24:48,700 --> 00:24:51,500
I will fight for
my love for you.

463
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:55,367
Noah, please.

464
00:24:56,367 --> 00:24:59,000
I've already made my decision.

465
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:02,200
Just respect it.

466
00:25:03,033 --> 00:25:06,267
Why is it so easy for you to
turn your back on me, Felma?

467
00:25:06,400 --> 00:25:08,933
Is that really how you feel?

468
00:25:09,067 --> 00:25:13,167
It's not easy to let go of
someone important to you!

469
00:25:13,300 --> 00:25:15,000
It's guilt-ridden.

470
00:25:16,300 --> 00:25:18,900
It hurts. It's hard!

471
00:25:19,033 --> 00:25:20,100
But...

472
00:25:21,433 --> 00:25:23,467
I can't force it.

473
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:26,167
I just can't force it.

474
00:25:26,300 --> 00:25:28,700
Because that would
be unfair to me.

475
00:25:28,833 --> 00:25:31,433
How many times do
I have to tell you?

476
00:25:31,567 --> 00:25:36,233
What can I do to
make you understand?

477
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:38,400
I won't give up.
I don't want to!

478
00:25:39,467 --> 00:25:42,267
I won't just walk
away without a fight.

479
00:25:42,833 --> 00:25:44,600
Felma, I love you so much.

480
00:25:44,733 --> 00:25:47,400
And I'll do everything to make
you love me again.

481
00:25:47,533 --> 00:25:48,500
Please, Felma.

482
00:25:48,633 --> 00:25:49,800
- I love you so much, Felma.
- Enough! Please.

483
00:25:49,933 --> 00:25:51,033
You're just drunk!

484
00:25:51,167 --> 00:25:52,067
Please, Felma.

485
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:53,167
Love me.

486
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:54,100
Let go of me!

487
00:25:54,233 --> 00:25:57,033
- Please, Felma!
- Let go of me, Noah!

488
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:59,067
Uncle Noah!

489
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:00,900
Let go of me, Noah!

490
00:26:01,033 --> 00:26:03,033
He wouldn't do that on purpose.

491
00:26:03,167 --> 00:26:04,500
He was just drunk...

492
00:26:04,633 --> 00:26:06,900
That's no excuse, Andrea.

493
00:26:07,033 --> 00:26:09,867
Didn't you push him
away first, Mom?

494
00:26:10,033 --> 00:26:12,267
You're blaming me?

495
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:13,733
Maybe you're happy?

496
00:26:13,867 --> 00:26:15,433
Because I'm leaving.

497
00:26:15,567 --> 00:26:17,033
You're the only one
thinking that way.

498
00:26:17,167 --> 00:26:20,000
By the way, your budget
for three days is on my vanity.

499
00:26:20,133 --> 00:26:22,633
Alright then, I have to go.

500
00:26:22,767 --> 00:26:25,100
Why can't you understand
my decision?

501
00:26:25,233 --> 00:26:27,300
It would be easy to understand

502
00:26:27,433 --> 00:26:30,000
if the guy who left you
wasn't involved.

503
00:26:30,133 --> 00:26:31,300
Manuel again?

504
00:26:31,433 --> 00:26:33,033
- Still him?
- Yes, Mom!

505
00:26:33,167 --> 00:26:34,233
Still him!

506
00:26:35,333 --> 00:26:36,600
Wait, why do you
have luggage?

507
00:26:36,733 --> 00:26:37,333
Are you leaving?

508
00:26:37,467 --> 00:26:38,433
Dad, it's us.

509
00:26:38,567 --> 00:26:39,500
Where are we going?

510
00:26:39,633 --> 00:26:40,633
Now's the perfect time.

511
00:26:40,767 --> 00:26:43,000
We'll run away while
Mom's not around.
